  "prompt_text": "Design a crisis intervention system that integrates real-time data analysis with human empathy. What can be automated and what cannot?",
  "response_text": "Title: Empathetic Crisis Intervention System (ECIS)\n\n1. System Overview:\n   The Empathetic Crisis Intervention System (ECIS) is a comprehensive, AI-driven crisis intervention platform designed to provide immediate assistance to individuals in distress. It integrates real-time data analysis with human empathy to deliver personalized and effective support.\n\n2. Key Components:\n\n   a. Real-time Data Analysis:\n      - Sentiment Analysis: Analyzing the emotional tone of the user's communication to identify the level of distress.\n      - Behavioral Analysis: Identifying patterns in the user's behavior, such as changes in communication frequency or content, to detect potential crises.\n      - Contextual Analysis: Understanding the user's environment, social network, and personal history to provide context-specific responses.\n\n   b. Human Empathy Integration:\n      - Emotional AI: Simulating human-like empathy by recognizing and responding to the user's emotional state.\n      - Personalized Responses: Tailoring responses to the user's unique needs, personality, and communication style.\n      - Active Listening: Allowing the user to express their feelings without interruption, providing a safe space for emotional release.\n\n3. Automated Functions:\n   - Real-time Data Analysis: Sentiment, behavioral, and contextual analysis.\n   - Initial Response Generation: Generating initial responses based on the analyzed data.\n   - Crisis Escalation Detection: Identifying when a user's situation requires human intervention.\n\n4. Non-Automated Functions:\n   - Deep Empathy: Simulating human-like empathy requires a level of understanding and emotional intelligence that is currently beyond the capabilities of AI. Therefore, human intervention will be necessary to provide the deep empathy required in crisis situations.\n   - Personalized Support: While AI can tailor responses to some extent, the nuances of personalized support may require human intervention to ensure the user feels truly understood and supported.\n   - Crisis Resolution: While AI can provide immediate assistance, resolving a crisis may require long-term support, which is best provided by human counselors or mental health professionals.\n\n5. Integration of Automated and Non-Automated Functions:\n   - The system will initially analyze the user's data and generate an initial response. If the user's situation is not critical, the AI can continue to provide support. If the situation is critical, the AI will escalate the case to a human counselor for further assistance.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directed",
